      • MESSAGE_TTL_IN_QUEUES

        public static java.lang.String MESSAGE_TTL_IN_QUEUES
        The MESSAGE_TTL_IN_QUEUES controls for how long a message published to the queues can live before it is discarded. A message that has been in the queue for longer than the configured TTL is said to be dead. This property must be a non-negative 32 bit integer (0 <= n <= 2^32-1), describing the TTL period in milliseconds.
